							</div>
					<div class="post-890 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized" id="post-890">
				<div class="posttitle">
			<h2><a href="http://romancingthestoveblog.wordpress.com/2010/05/16/dear-blog/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Dear&nbsp;Blog,">Dear&nbsp;Blog,</a></h2>
				<p class="postmetadata">May 16, 2010 by <a href="http://romancingthestoveblog.wordpress.com/author/awilliams9/" title="Posts by Anne">Anne</a>  </p>
				</div>

				<div class="entry">
					<p>Hello, It&#8217;s me, Anne.  Do you remember me?  My poor blog&#8230;I have neglected you.  I have not forgotten about you.  It is a classic case of &#8220;It&#8217;s not you, it&#8217;s me&#8221;.  Just after Easter, I came down with a cold that kicked my butt.  I was forced to stay in bed for 2 weeks.  I did not cook during that time, nor did I blog about the food I had made previous to falling ill.  Then, after recuperating, I started a new job, that has also kicked my butt.  I have come home tired, and felt completely uninspired in the kitchen.  However, now I am getting used to my new schedule, and feel that it is time to get back in the kitchen, and stop neglecting you, my blog.  Here&#8217;s to many more months of consistent blogging!</p>
<p>Sincerely,</p>
<p>Anne</p>
<div id="jp-post-flair" class="sharedaddy sd-like-enabled"></div>									</div>

